# Cinema 4D C++ Style Guide

Reference: https://developers.maxon.net/docs/cpp/2026_1_0/page_maxonapi_style_guide.html

## C++ Standard & Restrictions

- Target: C++20, but **no** concepts, coroutines, modules, or spaceship operator
- **Do not use the std library** (exceptions disabled by default). Use Maxon API equivalents:
  - `maxon::String` instead of `std::string`
  - `maxon::BaseArray` instead of `std::vector`
  - `maxon::UniqueRef` instead of `std::unique_ptr`
- Use `MAXON_LIKELY`/`MAXON_UNLIKELY` instead of `[[likely]]`/`[[unlikely]]`
- Use `MAXON_WARN_UNUSED` instead of `[[nodiscard]]`

## Data Types

Always use C4D types: `Int32`, `Int64`, `Int`, `Float32`, `Float64`, `Float`, `Bool`, `Char`, `String`, `Vector`, `Matrix`.
Use `Int` for indices and sizes. Avoid `unsigned` types unless clearly needed. Use `SIZEOF` instead of `sizeof`.

## Naming Conventions

- **Classes/Types**: UpperCamelCase, e.g. `MyNewClass`
- **Variables**: lowerCamelCase, e.g. `numErrors`, `polygonIndex`
- **Class member variables**: leading underscore, e.g. `_value`, `_index` (private/protected)
- **Global variables**: `g_` prefix, e.g. `g_var`
- **Constants/Macros/Enums**: ALL_CAPS, e.g. `MY_NUMBER`
- **Template parameters**: ALL_CAPS, use `typename` not `class`
- **Enum classes**: ALL_CAPS name, elements do not repeat the enum name
- Filenames: all lowercase, no spaces or special characters

## Formatting

- Tab width: 2, tabs only at beginning of lines
- Braces on their own line, aligned with `if`/`class`/`for`
- Always start a new line after `if`/`for`; no assignments inside `if`
- `switch`: indent `case` one level; each case must end with `break`/`return`/`MAXON_SWITCH_FALLTHROUGH`
- `public`/`protected`/`private` aligned with `class`
- Pointer asterisk grouped to type: `Int* ptr`
- `#if`/`#ifdef` directives start at column 0

## Class Design

- Layout order: public â†’ protected â†’ private; methods before data members
- Constructor only sets initial values; complex init goes in `Init()` method
- Single-argument constructors must use `explicit`
- Default to `MAXON_DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN`; implement `CopyFrom` when copying is needed
- Mark input reference parameters `const`; mark getter methods `const`

## Error Handling

- Every memory allocation must be checked
- Use `NewObj()`/`DeleteObj()` for objects, `NewMem()`/`DeleteMem()` for raw memory
- Floating-point division must check for zero divisor
- Watch for overflow in type conversions (especially Floatâ†’Int, Int32 multiplicationâ†’Int64)

## Other Key Points

- Use `constexpr` instead of `#define` for constants
- Use `static_cast`/`const_cast`/`reinterpret_cast` instead of C-style casts
- Avoid `goto`, floating-point for-loop increments, ANSI C routines (memset/printf etc.)
- Iterate containers with `const` reference: `for (const auto& item : container)`
- GUI operations must never run in a thread
- Prefer references and smart pointers over raw pointers
- Comments should describe "why", not "what"; avoid redundant comments
